- Added a new sub-pattern "Canonical `release` Check as a Dry-Run Validator of a Real Tag-Only Publish Pipeline" (ProjectScylla issue #2027): when a repo already HAS a real tag-only/workflow_dispatch-only OIDC PyPI publish pipeline (`release.yml`: bump-version â†’ GitHub Release â†’ build â†’ publish-pypi via `pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish`) and the canonical CI board needs a check-run named exactly `release` on PR/main, ship a dry-run pipeline VALIDATOR (`scripts/check_release_pipeline.py`, mirroring the repo's sibling check-script shape) rather than a no-op stub (fabricated pass), a republish (side effects), or a duplicate packaging job (sibling canonical `package`/`install` jobs already twine-check and install the artifact). The validator asserts: `on.push.tags` includes `v*` (handling the PyYAML `on:`â†’boolean-`True` key quirk via `workflow.get("on") or workflow.get(True)`); each publishing job's `if:` contains `startsWith(github.ref, 'refs/tags/v')` with the TestPyPI job gated on `workflow_dispatch`; publish jobs declare `permissions.id-token: write` plus the correct `environment` (pypi/testpypi) â€” the OIDC Trusted Publishing contract; `pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish` pinned to a full 40-hex SHA (`^pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish@[0-9a-f]{40}$`); and, with `--dist-dir`, a non-empty dist (refuse empty â€” no vacuous pass) containing â‰Ą1 wheel and â‰Ą1 sdist whose filename versions equal pyproject `[project].version` (replaying the pipeline's tagâ†”version check without a tag). Wired as a `release` job (job `name: release`) in the consolidated `_required.yml` (pull_request + push to main) with `needs: [build]`, downloading the `python-package` artifact â€” same shape as the canonical `test`/`package`/`install` jobs; emit-before-require (ruleset untouched); plus one CI step smoke-testing the dispatch path via `python scripts/bump_version.py patch --dry-run`.
