## v1.9.0 (2026-07-03)

**Changed by:** Myrmidons issue #750 planning session (canonical install CI check) â€” HomericIntelligence/Myrmidons ecosystem CI-naming rollout, PLANNING only (plan drafted; no code executed, no CI run).
**Verification:** unverified (plan-only). The frontmatter `verification` field stays `unverified`; the new sub-pattern is clearly labeled plan-only inline.

### What changed
- Added a new sub-pattern section, "Sub-Pattern: Canonical `install` Check for a Manifest/Dataset Repo (Real Check vs N/A)" (inserted before "## Failed Attempts"), capturing five plan-only lessons from Myrmidons #750: (1) "manifest repo â†’ install N/A" is usually wrong when the documented Quick-start IS an install surface (`pixi install` + `just install-hooks`) â€” a real check installs every locked environment, smoke-executes every pinned tool (`<tool> --version`), and runs the documented hook-install recipe end-to-end; (2) fetch the ecosystem convention doc itself via `gh api .../contents/... --jq .content | base64 -d` (works on private repos where raw WebFetch does not) â€” the doc's grouping rule showed existing `unit-tests` already maps to canonical `test` and the board badge is shields.io `check-runs/<repo>/main?nameFilter=<name>`, so the job MUST run on `push: branches: [main]` and the job `name:` field is the check-run name; (3) when an existing job overlaps the new canonical check (`deps/version-sync` already ran `pixi install --locked`), differentiate scope with a distinct superset-scope `install` job instead of renaming; (4) a canonical-check plan has a three-file blast radius (workflow + `docs/branch-protection.md` required-check registry + CLAUDE.md CI job list) plus an explicit POST-merge admin `gh api PATCH` registration step; (5) uncertain implementation-time assumptions for the reviewer: `pixi run -- <cmd> --version` arbitrary-command syntax, `just install-hooks` in a fresh CI checkout, the setup-pixi `.pixi` cache masking a broken lockfile resolve, and nested `pixi run` inside a just recipe.
- Extended the frontmatter description with trigger (10): a repo missing a canonical ecosystem CI check name (install/package/release) must choose between adding a REAL check vs documenting N/A â€” prefer a real check when the repo's documented quick-start install path IS an install surface, and verify the board's badge mechanism (check-runs on main) before picking the workflow/trigger.
- Added a Failed Attempts row: "Treat install as N/A for a dataset repo" â€” the documented quick-start IS an install surface; check the quick-start docs for an install path before declaring a canonical category N/A.
- Added tags `canonical-check-name`, `ecosystem-ci-board`, `manifest-repo-install`, `check-run-on-main`, `real-check-vs-na` (frontmatter + footer). Bumped frontmatter version 1.8.0 â†’ 1.9.0 (MINOR â€” new plan-only sub-pattern + new trigger + new Failed-Attempts row) and `date` 2026-07-02 â†’ 2026-07-03.

### Why
First application of the install-smoke-test trigger to a manifest/dataset repo choosing real-check vs N/A. The v1.8.0 install sub-pattern covered a C++ library's `cmake --install` + `find_package` contract; Myrmidons #750 forces the same canonical-`install` decision onto a repo with ZERO build artifacts, where the naive answer (N/A) hides a real, cheap smoke test of the documented developer install path. The board-badge mechanism (check-runs on main), the overlap-differentiation rule against `deps/version-sync`, and the three-file blast radius are durable, transferable planning facts for every future canonical-CI-naming rollout in the ecosystem.

