## v1.8.0 (2026-07-02)

**Changed by:** ProjectKeystone issue #596 / PR #600 install smoke-test check (IMPLEMENTATION learning â€” a NEW verified-local instance of the executable-convention-guard pattern applied to a C++ library's install/package-consumability contract, including a reviewer-demanded ALWAYS-ON self-test that exercises the guard's own failure branches on every CI run).
**Verification:** verified-local for THIS instance (the guard ran end-to-end inside the dev container: layout verification OK on the real prefix, the self-test's failure branches confirmed firing against a mutated throwaway copy, and the throwaway `find_package` consumer configured + compiled; BOTH negative paths were exercised deliberately). CI on ProjectKeystone PR #600 was still pending at capture time, so NOT verified-ci. The frontmatter `verification` field stays `unverified` because the weakest sub-patterns (#1506/#1507/#1516 and the #1543 allowlist reverse-check) remain plan-only; the new #596 material is clearly marked `verified-local` inline.

### What changed
- Added a new sub-pattern section, "Sub-Pattern: Install Smoke-Test Guard with Always-On Self-Test (verified-local instance: ProjectKeystone #596 / PR #600)." Documents the canonical `install` CI check for a pure C++ library as three stages in one reusable `scripts/check-install.sh` (mirroring the repo's check-*.sh gate convention): (a) `cmake --install <release-tree> --prefix <clean staging dir>`; (b) layout verification â€” required static archives, CMake package config files, and a BIDIRECTIONAL `diff` of source `include/` vs installed `include/keystone` header sets; (c) a throwaway consumer doing `find_package(Keystone CONFIG REQUIRED)` + compiling one TU including a self-contained public header, linked as a STATIC library because the prefix ships only the project's archives (PUBLIC third-party deps are not installed, so an executable link is impossible by design).
- Captured the central NEW lesson: an ALWAYS-ON self-test INSIDE the guard (reviewer-demanded, stronger than one-shot local mutation testing) â€” refactor layout checks into `verify_layout(prefix, label)`; after the real prefix passes, `cp -a` it to a throwaway dir, delete one installed header AND one archive, rerun `verify_layout` in a subshell and assert non-zero; delete the throwaway on success. Under `set -euo pipefail` with a forbid-`|| true` CI gate, capture the expected failure with `rc=0; ( verify_layout ... ) || rc=$?` â€” `|| rc=$?` is allowed where `|| true` is not.
- Captured the vacuous-green guard on mirror diffs (an empty-vs-empty `diff <(find A) <(find B)` passes â€” explicitly fail first if the installed header dir is missing or has no headers; generalizes the prefiltered-population-fixture lesson to the mirror check ITSELF), the IMPORTED_LOCATION gap (a STATIC find_package consumer never dereferences IMPORTED_LOCATION, so add a configure-time `foreach` over imported targets asserting `EXISTS "${_loc}"`, negative-verified by deleting an archive from a copied prefix), the failure-artifact enumeration rule (upload EVERY diagnostic dir the guard can leave behind â€” staging prefix, self-test throwaway, consumer build dir with CMakeError.log â€” with `if-no-files-found: ignore`), the .gitignore-swallow hazard (a repo-wide `install/` pattern silently hid the new `tests/install/` consumer dir from `git status`; fix with a `!tests/install/` negation and CONFIRM new guard files show as untracked), and the container-path coupling (`cmake_install.cmake` embeds container-absolute `/workspace/...` paths, so `cmake --install` and the consumer configure MUST run in the same container; the staging prefix under bind-mounted `build/` stays host-visible for artifact upload).
- Added a Failed Attempts row: local pre-commit fixers with a version-skewed clang-format reformatted UNTOUCHED files during guard verification â€” check the lint gate is green on main before accepting local hook verdicts on files you didn't change, and revert out-of-scope fixer churn (`git diff -- <files> | git apply -R`).
- Added an "Install-smoke-test generalization (v1.8.0, verified-local for the #596 instance)" note to Results & Parameters and a Verified On row (ProjectKeystone issue #596 / PR #600, verified-local).
- Extended the frontmatter description with trigger (9): adding an install/package-consumability CI gate (cmake --install layout check + find_package consumer compile) for a library, or needing a guard to exercise its own failure branches on every CI run via an always-on self-test against a mutated throwaway copy of its input.
- Added tags `install-smoke-test`, `self-test-in-guard`, `imported-location`, `find-package` (frontmatter + footer). Bumped frontmatter version 1.7.0 â†’ 1.8.0 (MINOR â€” new verified-local sub-pattern + a new Failed-Attempts row) and `date` 2026-06-30 â†’ 2026-07-02.

### Why
ProjectKeystone issue #596 / PR #600 is the first instance of this skill's pattern applied to a C++ install/package-consumability contract ("the installed package is consumable via find_package" previously lived only in prose/CI hope), and it surfaces genuinely new durable lessons: the always-on in-guard self-test against a mutated throwaway copy (which converts one-shot mutation testing into a permanent per-run property of the guard), the `|| rc=$?` idiom compatible with forbid-`|| true` gates, the vacuous-green hazard of empty-vs-empty mirror diffs, the STATIC-consumer IMPORTED_LOCATION blind spot and its configure-time closure, exhaustive failure-artifact enumeration, the .gitignore-swallow trap for new guard files, and container-path coupling of `cmake_install.cmake`. All were EXECUTED and verified locally in the dev container with both negative paths deliberately exercised; CI on PR #600 pending at capture time, so verified-local, not verified-ci.

### Previous version (v1.7.0) snapshot â€” changed sections
The full v1.7.0 rendered `.md` content prior to this amendment is preserved in git history at the parent commit of this amendment. This amendment is append-only outside the frontmatter: it appends one sub-pattern section (before "## Failed Attempts"), one Failed Attempts row, one Results & Parameters note, one Verified On row, and four footer tags. The only REWRITTEN section is the frontmatter; its v1.7.0 state was:

```yaml
